---
id: org.dxos.plugin.inbox
name: InboxPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

Unified inbox plugin for `DXOS` Composer — email, calendar, and contacts in one place, synced from Google and surfaced alongside workspace content.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |

## Types

```mdl
type MessageState
  literals: none | archived | deleted | spam
```

```mdl
type Filter
  fields:
    name: string
    filter: string              # query expression
```

```mdl
type Mailbox
  fields:
    name?: string
    feed: Ref<Feed>             # append-only Message stream
    labels?: Map<string, string>
    filters: Filter[]
    extractors?:
      enabled: string[]
      threshold: number         # 0..1 — AI confidence cutoff
```

```mdl
type Calendar
  fields:
    name?: string
    feed: Ref<Feed>             # append-only Event stream
```

```mdl
type DraftMessage
  fields:
    subject?: string
    to?: string
    body?: string
    replyTo?: Ref<Message>
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>
```

```mdl
type Settings
  fields:
    threads?: boolean           # group messages by conversation
```

## Components

```mdl
component MailboxArticle
  desc: Inbox surface for a Mailbox — filterable message list with reading pane.
  props:
    subject: Mailbox
    settings: Settings
  state:
    selected?: Message
    activeFilter?: Filter
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode         # sync / compose / filter actions
  actions:
    selectMessage(message: Message)
    applyFilter(filter: Filter)
    compose()
    reply(message: Message)
    archive(message: Message)
  emits:
    onOpenContact(actor: Actor)
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────┬─────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar]    │                         │
    ├──────────────┤                         │
    │ filter chips │  reading pane           │
    │              │                         │
    │ message list │  (selected message      │
    │              │   + related contacts /  │
    │              │   events / threads)     │
    │              │                         │
    └──────────────┴─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component CalendarArticle
  desc: Day/week view of events from a Calendar with selectable event detail.
  props:
    subject: Calendar
  state:
    selected?: Event
    range: { from: Date; to: Date }
  actions:
    selectEvent(event: Event)
    sync()
```

```mdl
component EditMessage
  desc: Compose / reply / forward editor for a DraftMessage.
  props:
    draft: DraftMessage
  actions:
    send()
    saveDraft()
    discard()
  emits:
    onSent(message: Message)
```

## Operations

Effectful operations — mutate persistent state or call external services.

```mdl
op addMailbox
  desc: Adds a Mailbox to the active space or collection.
  input:
    object: Mailbox
    target: Database | Collection
  output: string                # DXN of created Mailbox
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op draftEmail
  desc: Creates a new draft email scoped to a mailbox.
  input:
    subject: string
    to: string
    body: string
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>
    replyTo?: Ref<Message>
  output: string                # DXN of new draft Message
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op readEmail
  desc: Reads recent messages from a mailbox as a single text payload.
  input:
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>
    skip?: number
    limit?: number
  output: string                # rendered message content
  effects: [echo:read, feed:read]
```

```mdl
op classifyEmail
  desc: Picks an appropriate tag for a message from the database's tag set.
  input:
    message: Message
  output: string                # selected tag DXN, or void if none matched
  effects: [echo:read]
  requires: [AiService]
```

```mdl
op googleMailSync
  desc: Pulls messages from Gmail into the mailbox feed.
  input:
    integration: Ref<Integration>
    mailbox?: Ref<Mailbox>      # when omitted, syncs every mailbox on the Integration
    label?: string              # Gmail label (default: inbox)
    after?: number | string     # unix or yyyy-MM-dd
  output: number                # newMessages count
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op googleCalendarSync
  desc: Pulls events from Google Calendar into the calendar feed.
  input:
    integration: Ref<Integration>
    calendar?: Ref<Calendar>
    syncBackDays?: number
    syncForwardDays?: number
  output: number                # newEvents count
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op googleContactsSync
  desc: Pulls contacts from a Google contact group into Person objects.
  input:
    integration: Ref<Integration>
    contactGroupResourceName?: string
  output: number                # upserted count
  effects: [echo:write, http]
```

```mdl
op gmailSend
  desc: Sends a Message via Gmail using integration credentials.
  input:
    message: Message
    integration: Ref<Integration>
  output: string                # remote Gmail thread id
  effects: [http]
```

```mdl
op extractMessage
  desc: Runs configured AI extractors over a message; creates/updates structured objects.
  input:
    message: Message
    extractorId?: string        # specific extractor; default runs all enabled
  output:
    extractorId: string
    created: number
    updated: number
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [AiService]
```

```mdl
op extractContact
  desc: Extracts a Person object from an Actor referenced in a message.
  input:
    actor: Actor
  effects: [echo:write]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Mailbox

  req F-1.1: Mailbox stores messages in an append-only Feed; never mutates past entries.
  req F-1.2: Messages render newest-first with sender, subject, snippet, and timestamp.
  req F-1.3:
    when: settings.threads is true
    then: list groups messages by conversation; shows most recent per thread
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Calendar

  req F-2.1: Calendar stores events in an append-only Feed.
  req F-2.2: Day and week views render events ordered by start time.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Google Sync

  req F-3.1:
    when: user adds a Google Integration with mail scope
    then: op:googleMailSync runs and populates the mailbox feed

  req F-3.2:
    when: user adds a Google Integration with calendar scope
    then: op:googleCalendarSync runs and populates the calendar feed

  req F-3.3:
    when: user adds a Google Integration with contacts scope
    then: op:googleContactsSync upserts Person objects into the space

  req F-3.4: Subsequent syncs use server-side delta tokens; only new/changed records are written.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Compose & Send

  req F-4.1:
    when: user clicks compose / reply / forward
    then: op:draftEmail creates a DraftMessage; EditMessage opens for editing

  req F-4.2:
    when: user sends a draft
    then: op:gmailSend dispatches via the linked Google Integration
    errors: [SendFailed, NoIntegration]
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Filters and Labels

  req F-5.1: User can save a named filter expression on the mailbox.
  req F-5.2:
    when: a saved filter is selected
    then: message list shows only matching messages
```

```mdl
feat F-6: AI Assistance

  req F-6.1: Plugin contributes an Inbox blueprint with read / draft / classify / sync / extract tools.
  req F-6.2:
    when: agent calls op:classifyEmail on a message
    then: best-matching tag is applied; no tag applied below extractors.threshold

  req F-6.3:
    when: agent calls op:extractMessage on a confirmation email
    then: structured objects (e.g. Trip segments) are created or updated
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Related Content

  req F-7.1:
    when: a message is selected
    then: related contacts, events, and thread messages are shown alongside the reading pane

  req F-7.2:
    when: user clicks a related contact
    then: navigation opens the Person object
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Sync Gmail into mailbox
  given: a Mailbox linked to a Google Integration with valid credentials
  when: op:googleMailSync runs
  then:
    - newMessages > 0 on first run
    - Mailbox.feed contains Message entries ordered by received-at
```

```mdl
test T-2: Save and apply filter
  given: Mailbox open with > 1 messages, including one from alice@example.com
  when: user saves filter "from:alice@example.com" and selects it
  then:
    - message list shows only messages matching the filter
```

```mdl
test T-3: Draft and send reply
  given: a Message is selected in the mailbox
  when: user clicks reply, edits the body, and sends
  then:
    - op:draftEmail creates a DraftMessage with replyTo set
    - op:gmailSend dispatches via the linked Integration
    - sent message appears in the mailbox feed on next sync
```

```mdl
test T-4: Classify message
  given: a Message and a tag set with confidence threshold 0.7
  when: op:classifyEmail runs
  then:
    - if best tag confidence ≥ 0.7, tag applied
    - otherwise no tag applied
```

```mdl
test T-5: Extract confirmation
  given: a flight booking confirmation email
  when: op:extractMessage runs with the trip extractor enabled
  then:
    - Trip segment objects created or updated
    - extractMessage output reports created/updated counts
```

